# Introduction

The main change in this release is that the Qt GUI has been ported to Qt 5.
This brings many new possibilities in terms of QML widgets that can be used
in the interface.

# New in this release

## Enhancements

- Porting to Qt 5. As a side effect the PyQt code has been simplified
  substantially.
- Now it is possible to change the attenuation factor used in alpha-by-width
  coloring scheme after the targets have been added to the scene.

## CLI Changes

- Extended the --alpha-by-width option to admit an optional attenuation factor.
  The syntax is alpha-by-witdh\@attn where attn is a floating point number.
